history.text: What did you think of the Toy Story movie?  I loved it!
I really liked it too! I liked that Tom Hankds voiced Woody because he's one of my favorite actors.
I agree, Tom Hanks is awesome.  I also liked Tim Allen as Buzz Lightyear.
Do you typically like animated movies?
I do!  Especially Pixar movies.
Me too! I didn't realize Steve Jobs was involved in the production of Toy Story.
oh right, that's true, he had a big hand in Pixar's early life.  The critics sure loved Toy Story as well.
They did - it has great ratings and I completely agree with the critics on this one. It's a great movie for both children and adults.
"a work of genius"  yes, yes it was.  :-)
Definitely! I loved seeing Woody and Buzz go from rivals to friends.
I liked all the toy characters, they had really good comraderie
Which was your favorite? I think I liked Slinky Dog best!
hm, i liked Buzz.  He's got such a big ego and big heart too!
True. I liked that they threw a little romance in between him and Bo Peep the shepherdress.

Yes that was cute.  and how Mr Potato
 Head is wishing for Mrs Potato Head
I don't think I ever had a fav toy that lastest year after year.
Me either, so I can understand why the toys were nervous that they felt they were going to be replaced. I always replaced my toys.
oh, do you remember the bad neighbor kid Sid?  i remember some kids on my street growing up that liked to wreck action figures like that too.
hello?  are you still there?
darn.  ok, bye bye!
